<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><lyrics>[V1]
 I can't imagine how much You love me!
 Your love runs over
 The strings of my heart

[V2]
 And if I look into my eyes
 I'll find You crying
 And dying because of me

[V3]
 I'm sure there is no highest mountain
 Not the deepest valley I know
 That will separate from You

[V4]
 When I cry, oh My Lord
 You will collect my tears
 And hide them into Your heart

[V5]
 And all I need is Your smile
 To light this old dark night
 That was inside of me

[V6]
 I please You Lord, don't leave me alone
 There is full joy in walking along with You
 I know You know: I love You!</lyrics>
<title>How much you love me</title>
<author>Marco Prezioso</author>
<hymn_number>1694</hymn_number>
</song>